getLogFileName(25.10)                                    getLogFileName(25.10)

Name
       getLogFileName - Reports the name of the log file

Syntax
        getLogFileName [-help] [-fullPath]

       Reports the name of the log file.

       You  can  use  the getLogFileName command at any time during an Innovus
       session.

Parameters
       -help  Prints a brief description that includes the  type  and  default
              information for each getLogFileName parameter.

              For a detailed description of the command and all of its parame-
              ters, use the man command:

              man getLogFileName.

       -fullPath
              Reports the complete path to the log file.

Examples
              * The following command reports the name of the log file for the
                current Innovus session:

                getLogFileName

                The software reports:

                innovus.log1003

              * The  following  command  reports  the complete path to the log
                file for the current Innovus session:

                getLogFileName -fullPath

                The software reports:

                /icd/soclinx23/output/linux/07.10-e028_1/ph_46_08h34sec/in-
                novus.log1003

Related Information
              * innovus

